Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows significantly elevated creatinine, marked proteinuria, glucosuria, and ketonuria, with low urine specific gravity and low serum COâ‚‚, suggesting impaired renal function with possible acute or chronic kidney disease and metabolic acidosis. Urine findings (cloudy, brown, ammoniacal) may indicate underlying urinary tract pathology. Blood glucose and HbA1c are normal, making diabetes less likely. Recommend urgent nephrology evaluation and further workup for renal and urinary tract disorders.
